---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About | 0daysec Security Research">
  <section class="py-8">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-display text-white mb-6">About 0daysec Advisory</h1>
      
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <p>
          The 0daysec Advisory database is a collection of security vulnerability reports and technical writeups published by 0daysec security researchers. 
          Our mission is to contribute to the security community by discovering, responsibly disclosing, and documenting security issues that affect popular software and systems.
        </p>
        
        <h2>Our Research Methodology</h2>
        
        <p>
          Our security research follows these key principles:
        </p>
        
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Thorough Analysis:</strong> We conduct in-depth analysis of systems and applications to identify potential security weaknesses.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Ethical Approach:</strong> We follow responsible disclosure practices, always notifying vendors before public disclosure.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Technical Precision:</strong> Our advisories provide detailed technical information to help understand the nature of vulnerabilities.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Remediation Focus:</strong> We include clear information about patches and mitigations when available.
          </li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2>Contact Information</h2>
        
        <p>
          For security researchers and journalists: If you have questions about our published advisories or would like to discuss our research, please reach out to us via:
        </p>
        
        <ul>
          <li>Email: research@zerodaysec.org</li>
          <li>Twitter: <a href="https://twitter.com/0daysec">@0daysec</a></li>
          <li>GitHub: <a href="https://github.com/odaysec">github.com/odaysec</a></li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2>Legal Disclaimer</h2>
        
        <p>
          The information contained in these security advisories is for educational purposes only. It is meant to help system administrators, security professionals, and developers understand security issues and apply appropriate fixes. 
        </p>
        
        <p>
          All vulnerability research is conducted in accordance with ethical guidelines and applicable laws. We explicitly condemn any use of this information for malicious purposes or illegal activities.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>